name: 3-(methylsulfinyl)phenylacetic acid
Reason: The compound 3-(methylsulfinyl)phenylacetic acid has a sulfur atom, which is known to increase the melting point due to its high electronegativity and ability to form strong intermolecular bonds. The methyl group also adds some steric hindrance, which can further increase the melting point. Additionally, the carboxylic acid functional group can participate in hydrogen bonding, which can also contribute to the melting point.
